WEBVTT

00:01:15.389 --> 00:01:16.765
Sun Han-gyul.

00:01:18.851 --> 00:01:20.436
That's his name.

00:01:25.941 --> 00:01:27.401
I'll come back for you.

00:01:28.569 --> 00:01:29.862
I'll come for you two.

00:01:40.414 --> 00:01:41.290
EPISODE 7

00:01:41.373 --> 00:01:46.128
The number you have dialed is unavailable.
Please leave a voicemail after the beep.

00:01:48.047 --> 00:01:49.256
I told you clearly.

00:01:50.841 --> 00:01:52.509
If I don't hear from you today...

00:01:54.011 --> 00:01:55.095
you're dead to me.

00:01:57.348 --> 00:01:58.557
From now on,

00:02:00.100 --> 00:02:01.268
you're nobody to me.

00:02:02.561 --> 00:02:04.480
I'm erasing your name,
your face, everything.

00:02:06.649 --> 00:02:08.651
EDIT - DELETE

00:02:08.734 --> 00:02:09.610
DELETE?
YES

00:02:20.663 --> 00:02:21.497
YES
NO

00:02:21.580 --> 00:02:23.123
BIG SIS

00:02:27.461 --> 00:02:32.967
THAT WOMAN

00:02:37.680 --> 00:02:39.598
I...

00:02:40.224 --> 00:02:42.184
I haven't even touched
your fingernail, but...

00:02:43.519 --> 00:02:44.687
But you had...

00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:47.690
coffee with her...

00:02:49.733 --> 00:02:50.859
and held hands with her.

00:02:54.738 --> 00:02:55.656
So…

00:02:58.075 --> 00:03:00.369
you were mad at me because of that?

00:03:01.662 --> 00:03:04.832
You told me to trust you,
and you did that with another woman.

00:03:06.166 --> 00:03:07.376
You're right, Ms. Bom.

00:03:10.379 --> 00:03:11.296
What?

00:03:13.257 --> 00:03:14.341
I, Sun Jae-gyu...

00:03:16.343 --> 00:03:17.845
don't keep my word.

00:03:18.637 --> 00:03:20.180
I'm not as strong as I look,

00:03:21.974 --> 00:03:26.186
and I'm not intelligent, cultured,
refined or patient.

00:03:31.734 --> 00:03:32.693
I'm sorry.

00:03:35.195 --> 00:03:36.363
I can't wait any longer.

00:04:48.727 --> 00:04:49.561
Ms. Bom.

00:04:50.312 --> 00:04:51.188
Ms. Bom.

00:04:51.939 --> 00:04:53.565
Ms. Bom!

00:04:58.737 --> 00:04:59.571
Ms. Bom.

00:05:00.364 --> 00:05:03.408
I'm not normally like this.

00:05:04.493 --> 00:05:07.788
Why are you so impatient?

00:05:09.289 --> 00:05:10.207
I'm sorry.

00:05:11.083 --> 00:05:14.503
A man's fiery heart
can only take so much. Gosh.

00:05:14.586 --> 00:05:15.504
Well,

00:05:16.505 --> 00:05:19.133
the one who started the fire
is partly responsible.

00:05:20.551 --> 00:05:23.387
Let's not talk about this anymore.

00:05:25.848 --> 00:05:26.682
But...

00:05:30.853 --> 00:05:33.272
you've got to tell me who she is.

00:05:36.066 --> 00:05:38.277
Who is she? An ex?

00:05:39.153 --> 00:05:41.488
A female friend? Or...

00:05:42.823 --> 00:05:43.907
your current girlfriend?

00:05:45.159 --> 00:05:46.160
Absolutely not.

00:05:46.243 --> 00:05:47.286
Then who is she?

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:53.876
She's actually...

00:05:57.462 --> 00:05:59.339
-from insurance.
-From insurance?

00:06:00.632 --> 00:06:02.509
Who gets that close
with an insurance agent?

00:06:03.177 --> 00:06:04.469
Which type of insurance?

00:06:05.095 --> 00:06:06.763
What type of coverage is it?

00:06:08.765 --> 00:06:09.641
Well...

00:06:10.934 --> 00:06:12.144
What was it called?

00:06:13.812 --> 00:06:15.439
Actual expense health insurance.

00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:18.734
She said people live to be 100 these days,

00:06:18.817 --> 00:06:20.652
so I can't go without health insurance.

00:06:20.736 --> 00:06:23.572
Apparently, she's known as

00:06:24.156 --> 00:06:25.991
the Doberman of the insurance world.

00:06:26.074 --> 00:06:27.784
Once she bites, she never lets go.

00:06:27.868 --> 00:06:29.703
So, did she bite you?

00:06:29.786 --> 00:06:31.914
Come on, Ms. Bom.

00:06:32.831 --> 00:06:35.709
I'm the kind of guy
who's basically insurance himself.

00:06:36.251 --> 00:06:38.587
I never get sick,
so why bother with insurance?

00:06:38.670 --> 00:06:39.880
Then she'll come back.

00:06:41.715 --> 00:06:42.549
That won't happen.

00:06:44.718 --> 00:06:45.969
If that woman comes back...

00:06:49.973 --> 00:06:51.016
I told you clearly.

00:06:52.976 --> 00:06:54.978
I erased your name, your face, everything.

00:06:56.605 --> 00:06:59.483
If you show up around here again...

00:07:02.819 --> 00:07:03.946
you're dead.

00:07:07.199 --> 00:07:08.909
All right, I understand.

00:07:12.621 --> 00:07:15.540
So, we're good now?

00:07:19.127 --> 00:07:23.006
I just need to wait two years
as we promised.

00:07:25.008 --> 00:07:26.218
Yes, two years.

00:07:27.594 --> 00:07:30.305
Right, two years.

00:07:33.433 --> 00:07:34.268
You should go.

00:07:35.269 --> 00:07:37.396
Sure. I'm off, then.

00:07:45.862 --> 00:07:48.156
-By the way...
-Yes, what is it?

00:07:48.949 --> 00:07:52.411
Don't we get a vacation or something?

00:07:53.620 --> 00:07:54.830
-A vacation?
-Yes.

00:07:55.539 --> 00:07:56.999
What's a vacation for?

00:07:57.082 --> 00:07:59.167
Well, you see,

00:07:59.251 --> 00:08:02.004
vacations are meant to
improve productivity, right?

00:08:02.087 --> 00:08:02.963
So...

00:08:04.256 --> 00:08:08.218
if I could just spend a day with you,

00:08:08.302 --> 00:08:10.304
eat some good food, and go on a date,

00:08:11.138 --> 00:08:15.600
I think I could patiently wait
for two years.

00:08:21.690 --> 00:08:22.566
Or maybe not?

00:08:25.694 --> 00:08:27.237
Just for a day, right?

00:08:27.946 --> 00:08:28.822
Yes.

00:08:30.657 --> 00:08:33.493
Just one day after Green Narae wraps up?

00:08:33.577 --> 00:08:35.954
You got it! Just one day.

00:08:41.501 --> 00:08:43.420
Are you really going to Shinsu?

00:08:43.503 --> 00:08:45.380
What do you mean, "stop"?

00:08:45.464 --> 00:08:48.884
My daughter, whom I haven't heard from
in over a year, called me at 7:48 a.m.

00:08:48.967 --> 00:08:50.844
asking for tickets
to Song Ga-in's concert.

00:08:50.927 --> 00:08:52.596
How could I stop? I should go for it.

00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:56.892
You got the wrong signal,
so back up first.

00:08:58.852 --> 00:09:01.063
What's going on?

00:09:01.146 --> 00:09:05.525
I thought Bom's sudden change of heart
was all part of your big picture.

00:09:12.824 --> 00:09:14.117
You said earlier,

00:09:14.993 --> 00:09:18.955
that if anything came up,
I should make sure to hire you.

00:09:22.042 --> 00:09:24.795
Unfortunately, I did...

00:09:25.754 --> 00:09:26.588
say that.

00:09:27.381 --> 00:09:31.551
I'd like to officially hire you
to handle the settlement...

00:09:33.887 --> 00:09:35.263
for Sun Jae-gyu's assault case.

00:09:39.643 --> 00:09:42.979
I was trying to draw the big picture,

00:09:43.063 --> 00:09:45.690
but my pencil slipped for a moment.

00:09:45.774 --> 00:09:49.194
How distracted were you
for your pencil to slip?

00:09:50.362 --> 00:09:52.072
There's no need to rush.

00:09:52.155 --> 00:09:54.699
If you can't do it,
just give me the address.

00:09:55.283 --> 00:09:56.576
I've already packed up,

00:09:56.660 --> 00:10:00.205
so I'll go myself
and finish this face to face.

00:10:02.124 --> 00:10:03.834
Are you saying you can't trust me?

00:10:03.917 --> 00:10:06.586
Do you want a monthly report or something?

00:10:10.215 --> 00:10:12.259
Do you actually have a plan?

00:10:14.302 --> 00:10:15.971
So the thief

00:10:16.054 --> 00:10:19.057
got caught red-handed
in Jjang-gu's chili field?

00:10:19.141 --> 00:10:20.225
Who was it?

00:10:20.308 --> 00:10:22.686
Who took it all,
the meju and the gold medal?

00:10:22.769 --> 00:10:24.187
-A deer.
-A deer?

00:10:24.271 --> 00:10:26.398
There was a deer in the field...

00:10:26.481 --> 00:10:28.066
-Yeah.
-...and its neck was shining.

00:10:28.150 --> 00:10:29.484
-My goodness.
-It turns out

00:10:29.568 --> 00:10:31.987
it was wearing
Dong-pyo's grandma's gold medal.

00:10:32.070 --> 00:10:33.405
My goodness.

00:10:35.323 --> 00:10:36.950
We blamed the wrong person.

00:10:37.033 --> 00:10:38.326
That could've been bad.

00:10:40.078 --> 00:10:42.247
My goodness. Look at that.

00:10:42.330 --> 00:10:43.665
Isn't that Mr. Evil Thoughts?

00:11:05.729 --> 00:11:07.647
Oh, dear. That's terrifying.

00:11:10.692 --> 00:11:12.944
It's such a beautiful day today!

00:11:15.071 --> 00:11:19.367
He plowed the field in the scorching sun.
Did the sun fry his brain?

00:11:19.451 --> 00:11:22.496
He's smiling like an idiot.
Where's he going?

00:11:34.841 --> 00:11:38.762
He graduated top of his class
in law at Hanguk University.

00:11:38.845 --> 00:11:41.765
He also finished
the 47th Judicial Training Institute

00:11:41.848 --> 00:11:44.100
at the top of his class.

00:11:46.353 --> 00:11:49.814
He was recognized for his exceptional
talent as a junior lawyer

00:11:50.774 --> 00:11:52.984
at Law Firm Sujun,

00:11:53.068 --> 00:11:56.321
winning the Outstanding New Lawyer Award.

00:11:59.824 --> 00:12:01.701
There's still a lot left.

00:12:01.785 --> 00:12:03.912
If you're going to go over
my whole résumé,

00:12:03.995 --> 00:12:06.122
your voice might give out, Mr. Hong.

00:12:18.134 --> 00:12:19.636
"Meet a successful professional."

00:12:20.554 --> 00:12:23.181
What do you all think success is?

00:12:24.099 --> 00:12:27.102
Here's what I think success really is.

00:12:29.854 --> 00:12:30.897
SOMEONE ON MY SIDE

00:12:36.653 --> 00:12:37.654
"Someone on my side"?

00:12:41.825 --> 00:12:43.868
Having someone fully on your side,

00:12:44.703 --> 00:12:46.746
is there anything
more successful than that?

00:12:48.123 --> 00:12:50.458
When I meet a client for the first time,

00:12:50.542 --> 00:12:52.711
I always start with this promise.

00:12:54.754 --> 00:12:56.506
"I'll be on your side."

00:13:08.518 --> 00:13:10.687
We all face unfair situations at times.

00:13:12.606 --> 00:13:14.941
Sometimes, people you trusted
turn their backs on you,

00:13:16.359 --> 00:13:18.486
and it feels like no one's on your side.

00:13:22.115 --> 00:13:22.949
Don't.

00:13:24.034 --> 00:13:26.161
Completely being on your side.

00:13:27.203 --> 00:13:30.498
That's what being a lawyer is all about.

00:13:46.890 --> 00:13:47.724
Uncle.

00:13:51.895 --> 00:13:53.021
I need a small favor.

00:13:53.647 --> 00:13:57.150
Could you order some nice galbi
for the Green Narae field trip?

00:14:03.198 --> 00:14:04.491
Come on!

00:14:06.576 --> 00:14:08.161
What? Why?

00:14:08.244 --> 00:14:09.871
Did you lose some muscle in your jaw?

00:14:09.954 --> 00:14:12.082
You've been going around
with that grin lately.

00:14:12.165 --> 00:14:15.543
Why? Everyone keeps saying
something's off about me.

00:14:19.756 --> 00:14:20.840
See for yourself.

00:14:28.223 --> 00:14:30.225
Why on earth
are you walking around like that?

00:14:33.853 --> 00:14:35.146
The truth is,

00:14:35.855 --> 00:14:37.065
after this field trip,

00:14:38.233 --> 00:14:40.235
I'm going on a date for one day
with Ms. Bom.

00:14:42.362 --> 00:14:44.656
Just imagine going on a date with Se-jin.

00:14:44.739 --> 00:14:46.282
Could you stop smiling?

00:14:47.367 --> 00:14:48.493
Well, I get that.

00:14:50.328 --> 00:14:52.539
Ms. Bom might be turned off
if you act like this.

00:14:52.622 --> 00:14:54.249
Why would she get turned off?

00:14:57.419 --> 00:15:01.297
Se-jin's brother came to school today,
all dressed up in a suit.

00:15:02.048 --> 00:15:05.719
Even with all those people watching,
he stayed composed and spoke perfectly.

00:15:05.802 --> 00:15:09.013
Everyone in the auditorium was so moved
that they gave him a standing ovation.

00:15:09.097 --> 00:15:12.100
I have no plans for college,
yet I almost wanted to be a lawyer.

00:15:12.183 --> 00:15:13.268
What about Ms. Bom?

00:15:13.768 --> 00:15:15.353
Did she give a standing ovation too?

00:15:15.437 --> 00:15:16.938
She clapped the most.

00:15:23.486 --> 00:15:24.738
To be honest,

00:15:26.156 --> 00:15:29.284
you won't be an official couple
for another two years.

00:15:29.367 --> 00:15:32.287
Until then, she's free to date anyone.

00:15:33.121 --> 00:15:36.958
So stop acting silly
and tone down the grin.

00:15:37.584 --> 00:15:38.668
Got it?

00:15:41.171 --> 00:15:42.255
Got it.

00:15:43.965 --> 00:15:46.843
So your teacher gave a standing ovation
to Choi I-jun?

00:15:47.802 --> 00:15:49.596
Watch closely on this field trip.

00:15:49.679 --> 00:15:51.765
See how your teacher reacts.

00:15:51.848 --> 00:15:53.850
-Got it?
-Got it.

00:16:03.735 --> 00:16:04.694
Enjoy.

00:16:08.448 --> 00:16:11.201
You know Choi I-jun, the lawyer?

00:16:12.368 --> 00:16:13.953
He pointed right at me

00:16:15.163 --> 00:16:16.623
and said, "I'll be on your side."

00:16:17.248 --> 00:16:20.794
Suddenly, I could barely breathe,
and my heart started racing like crazy.

00:16:21.753 --> 00:16:25.173
I heard he and Sun Jae-gyu
are the same age.

00:16:25.256 --> 00:16:27.383
And yet, they're completely different.

00:16:27.467 --> 00:16:29.719
-Right? The other day...
-Yes.

00:16:29.803 --> 00:16:33.014
...did you see Sun Jae-gyu
acting out in handcuffs?

00:16:33.097 --> 00:16:35.725
How could women flock to that thief?

00:16:35.809 --> 00:16:37.060
I just don't get it.

00:16:41.439 --> 00:16:44.150
I should set a few things straight.

00:16:44.943 --> 00:16:47.237
Mr. Sun isn't a thief.

00:16:47.320 --> 00:16:48.822
He was trying to catch the thief.

00:16:48.905 --> 00:16:53.284
The woman you saw
isn't Mr. Sun's girlfriend.

00:16:53.368 --> 00:16:54.494
She's an insurance agent.

00:16:55.995 --> 00:16:57.038
An insurance agent?

00:16:57.705 --> 00:16:59.332
Come on, that's ridiculous.

00:16:59.415 --> 00:17:00.583
Mr. Wi, you saw them.

00:17:01.459 --> 00:17:03.336
The way they were looking at each other,

00:17:03.419 --> 00:17:06.214
did that look like an insurance agent
and a client to you?

00:17:06.297 --> 00:17:08.967
If I had to describe the look in her eyes,

00:17:09.050 --> 00:17:11.886
it was like she was looking
at a priceless treasure.

00:17:11.970 --> 00:17:13.304
Good observation.

00:17:14.347 --> 00:17:17.600
Once she sets her mind on a client,
there is no letting go.

00:17:17.684 --> 00:17:20.228
So she's known as
the Doberman of the insurance world.

00:17:21.229 --> 00:17:22.438
Is that so?

00:17:23.231 --> 00:17:24.440
That's great.

00:17:24.524 --> 00:17:27.861
My gums have been acting up,
so I was going to get dental insurance.

00:17:27.944 --> 00:17:30.238
When's that insurance agent coming again?

00:17:31.114 --> 00:17:33.575
I hate to break it to you,
but there's no way

00:17:33.658 --> 00:17:35.535
she'll ever be back in this area.

00:17:37.370 --> 00:17:38.580
By the way, Ms. Bom,

00:17:39.455 --> 00:17:41.249
how did you know all that?

00:17:58.850 --> 00:18:00.310
Look at the time.

00:18:01.394 --> 00:18:04.022
I have a field trip, so I better go.

00:18:05.273 --> 00:18:07.358
-Answer before you go.
-She knows everything.

00:18:10.320 --> 00:18:11.613
Ms. Bom, we'll go ahead.

00:18:11.696 --> 00:18:12.822
-Okay.
-See you in a bit.

00:18:12.906 --> 00:18:14.073
-See you soon.
-Okay.

00:18:16.576 --> 00:18:17.410
Ms. Bom!

00:18:19.370 --> 00:18:20.288
Ms. Bom.

00:18:20.371 --> 00:18:22.707
Something's going on
with you and Sun Jae-gyu, right?

00:18:23.207 --> 00:18:24.542
Nothing's going on.

00:18:24.626 --> 00:18:26.336
My twins saw you the other day.

00:18:27.503 --> 00:18:28.546
Bom-sik!

00:18:34.886 --> 00:18:37.889
They saw him entering your place.

00:18:40.808 --> 00:18:43.519
I thought he was just a thug
with a dragon tattoo on his arm.

00:18:43.603 --> 00:18:45.939
But seeing him at the sports fest
and catching the thief,

00:18:46.022 --> 00:18:47.440
he's competitive and righteous.

00:18:47.523 --> 00:18:50.109
I realized he's not just a dumb guy.

00:18:50.193 --> 00:18:53.529
The more you're around him,
the more you want to stay close to him,

00:18:53.613 --> 00:18:55.156
am I right?

00:18:55.239 --> 00:18:57.367
He didn't come to my place
to get close to me.

00:18:57.450 --> 00:19:01.371
Well, the dog I adopted
was rescued by him.

00:19:01.454 --> 00:19:02.789
So he came by to check in.

00:19:03.706 --> 00:19:06.626
You've been looking really pretty lately.

00:19:07.460 --> 00:19:10.505
You totally have that dating glow.

00:19:12.590 --> 00:19:16.761
I hear you're going on a field trip
to where Han-gyul's uncle works.

00:19:17.971 --> 00:19:18.846
Ms. Seo.

00:19:19.472 --> 00:19:24.560
The purpose of our visit is strictly
for the Energy Club field trip...

00:19:26.980 --> 00:19:29.107
Oh, the bus is here.

00:19:29.190 --> 00:19:30.024
Well then...

00:19:34.487 --> 00:19:36.072
There's something going on.

00:19:39.367 --> 00:19:41.202
What if the students hear that at school?

00:19:41.828 --> 00:19:43.454
Pull yourself together, Yoon Bom.

00:19:43.538 --> 00:19:46.332
If the students find out, you're done for.

00:19:46.416 --> 00:19:49.419
When you see Mr. Sun today,
you need to be completely hostile

00:19:49.502 --> 00:19:51.004
and as cold as possible.

00:19:51.587 --> 00:19:54.674
Remember that feeling when
you first saw him with the chicken skewer.

00:19:58.720 --> 00:20:00.555
-Wow.
-Wow, it's so refreshing.

00:20:02.473 --> 00:20:03.808
I wish this land was mine.

00:20:03.891 --> 00:20:05.476
It's gigantic.

00:20:06.394 --> 00:20:07.645
Why is it so big?

00:20:07.729 --> 00:20:10.314
Wow, this place is insane.

00:20:10.398 --> 00:20:13.484
I don't see Mr. Sun here today.

00:20:14.318 --> 00:20:15.653
Oh, right.

00:20:16.612 --> 00:20:17.697
Him?

00:20:21.701 --> 00:20:24.704
This is Philip. Can you hear me?

00:20:24.787 --> 00:20:26.706
Current wind speed is fine.

00:21:00.907 --> 00:21:04.118
The nacelle's hooked up.
Rope's going down!

00:22:25.616 --> 00:22:26.826
All right.

00:22:28.911 --> 00:22:32.165
Welcome to our plant, Green Narae!

00:22:34.083 --> 00:22:37.336
Uncle, let me tell you something.
It was perfect.

00:22:37.420 --> 00:22:40.548
Master, I thought
I was watching an action film.

00:22:40.631 --> 00:22:42.091
What you just saw wasn't a movie.

00:22:42.175 --> 00:22:45.219
These wind turbines make wind energy,

00:22:45.887 --> 00:22:50.141
and the blades are prone to damage
from airborne objects or birds.

00:22:50.224 --> 00:22:54.478
That's why our plant constantly monitors
and maintains the turbines

00:22:54.562 --> 00:22:56.147
both on the ground and in the air.

00:22:58.107 --> 00:23:00.943
Ms. Bom,
I've got a new dream starting today.

00:23:01.027 --> 00:23:04.071
It's not to marry an idol,
