to be surrounded by a crowd

00:45:48.643 --> 00:45:51.187
than a restaurant
with just a few tables like before?

00:45:51.771 --> 00:45:53.189
And finals are coming up soon,

00:45:53.273 --> 00:45:55.525
so there's no way students
or teachers would come.

00:46:16.212 --> 00:46:17.171
What the heck?

00:46:18.339 --> 00:46:19.424
Wait, where did they go?

00:46:19.507 --> 00:46:21.968
Gosh, I'm still holding her purse.
Darn it.

00:46:29.100 --> 00:46:30.226
Do we have to try this?

00:46:31.853 --> 00:46:34.856
Ms. Bom.
Let's just do this one thing and leave.

00:46:34.939 --> 00:46:35.815
You know what?

00:46:36.316 --> 00:46:39.277
I've always wanted to go
to an amusement park with my boyfriend...

00:46:39.360 --> 00:46:40.820
Let's go in there.

00:46:40.903 --> 00:46:41.946
Let's go...

00:46:42.947 --> 00:46:44.157
Hye-suk.

00:46:45.450 --> 00:46:48.119
Ms. Seo. There's Ms. Seo!

00:46:52.081 --> 00:46:53.041
Busted.

00:46:57.879 --> 00:46:59.005
Hye-suk.

00:46:59.505 --> 00:47:01.215
I can't handle this with my weak heart.

00:47:01.966 --> 00:47:04.802
Wait, Hye-suk! Can't we not go in here?

00:47:07.597 --> 00:47:08.681
Darn it.

00:47:17.857 --> 00:47:19.317
What do we do? There...

00:47:21.444 --> 00:47:22.820
Release my grudges!

00:47:22.904 --> 00:47:24.030
No.

00:47:33.331 --> 00:47:34.290
Get out of the way.

00:47:42.465 --> 00:47:44.300
-Come in here.
-What?

00:47:44.967 --> 00:47:47.136
We should hide from Ms. Seo. Hurry.

00:47:58.439 --> 00:47:59.440
Ms. Bom.

00:48:00.066 --> 00:48:02.694
I know you're in here. I already saw you.

00:48:03.444 --> 00:48:04.862
-Where are you?
-Hye-suk.

00:48:05.488 --> 00:48:07.240
I don't think we should go here.

00:48:15.206 --> 00:48:16.124
Ms. Bom.

00:48:17.208 --> 00:48:18.209
Ms. Bom, where are you?

00:48:18.292 --> 00:48:20.169
Hye-suk, why are you looking for Ms. Bom?

00:48:30.763 --> 00:48:32.265
Ms. Bom.

00:48:32.348 --> 00:48:34.350
I know you're in here.

00:48:44.736 --> 00:48:46.154
Ms. Bom.

00:48:50.700 --> 00:48:51.534
Who are you?

00:48:51.617 --> 00:48:52.910
Release my grudges!

00:48:52.994 --> 00:48:56.080
Yes, right in there. Ms. Bom!

00:48:56.164 --> 00:48:57.331
Ms. Bom!

00:49:44.921 --> 00:49:45.797
Sun Han-gyul?

00:50:08.736 --> 00:50:10.655
I think we've done plenty for a date.

00:50:11.948 --> 00:50:13.282
Shall we head home now?

00:50:15.743 --> 00:50:16.953
Still, it's our first date.

00:50:17.912 --> 00:50:21.415
We didn't catch the sunrise
or enjoy a good restaurant.

00:50:23.793 --> 00:50:26.254
It's not like it was totally unexpected.

00:50:28.965 --> 00:50:33.219
I do wish we'd had
that amusement park date, just a little.

00:50:36.514 --> 00:50:38.140
You really wanted to go on the rides?

00:50:40.434 --> 00:50:45.898
I just wanted a normal,
typical date like everyone else.

00:50:49.777 --> 00:50:51.571
If that's what you want, we should do it.

00:50:53.531 --> 00:50:55.157
Yeah, come with me.

00:51:04.542 --> 00:51:06.127
Hop out.

00:51:10.298 --> 00:51:12.675
Welcome to Jae-gyu Land!

00:51:12.758 --> 00:51:14.468
What is this place?

00:51:14.552 --> 00:51:16.178
It's a closed-down elementary school.

00:51:16.262 --> 00:51:17.763
The playground's seen better days.

00:51:19.599 --> 00:51:22.518
Anyone who wants to go
on the Viking, come over here.

00:51:22.602 --> 00:51:23.436
Hey, you there.

00:51:24.020 --> 00:51:26.564
Hey, beautiful lady.
Aren't you going to ride the Viking?

00:51:26.647 --> 00:51:28.274
-Come on, quick.
-Okay.

00:51:28.774 --> 00:51:30.693
It's free.

00:51:32.111 --> 00:51:33.112
All right.

00:51:33.946 --> 00:51:36.032
Hold on to the safety bar.

00:51:37.617 --> 00:51:38.534
Here we go.

00:51:49.754 --> 00:51:51.672
Want me to go a little slower?

00:51:52.340 --> 00:51:53.507
No, go faster!

00:51:53.591 --> 00:51:54.967
-Faster?
-Yes.

00:51:55.051 --> 00:51:57.094
Okay! Hey, lady.

00:51:57.178 --> 00:51:58.596
There's no one around here.

00:51:58.679 --> 00:51:59.972
If you felt frustrated today,

00:52:00.056 --> 00:52:02.308
scream as much as you want, okay?

00:52:02.391 --> 00:52:03.225
Okay.

00:52:03.768 --> 00:52:04.727
Here we go!

00:52:29.001 --> 00:52:31.754
Hold on tight, or you'll fly off.

00:52:31.837 --> 00:52:32.964
Here we go!

00:53:10.918 --> 00:53:12.461
It's closing time.

00:53:12.962 --> 00:53:13.796
No way.

00:53:17.049 --> 00:53:18.718
Has it gotten this late already?

00:53:20.094 --> 00:53:22.054
Let's say goodbye here.

00:53:24.265 --> 00:53:26.142
Here, now?

00:53:31.689 --> 00:53:34.066
I have one last thing
I want to say to you.

00:53:34.734 --> 00:53:36.444
Can I just tell you three things?

00:53:37.069 --> 00:53:39.530
You see,
I don't care for getting all romantic--

00:53:39.613 --> 00:53:41.407
An average woman's BMR is 1,300 calories.

00:53:41.490 --> 00:53:44.577
Make sure to balance
your carbs, protein, and fat

00:53:44.660 --> 00:53:48.622
in a 5-3-2 ratio
based on your total calorie intake.

00:53:51.375 --> 00:53:53.794
Once it's past midnight,
you won't see me for two years.

00:53:53.878 --> 00:53:55.755
You're talking
about carbs, protein, and fat?

00:53:56.422 --> 00:53:58.841
I'm saying, eat well
even when you're alone.

00:53:59.550 --> 00:54:02.553
Take care of yourself
until the day we meet again.

00:54:04.430 --> 00:54:05.681
What about the second thing?

00:54:07.183 --> 00:54:10.561
There's bound to be at least one person
you feel like you want to kill.

00:54:10.644 --> 00:54:12.229
When that happens,

00:54:12.313 --> 00:54:15.441
just text me their name.

00:54:15.524 --> 00:54:16.734
Are you going to kill them?

00:54:16.817 --> 00:54:18.569
I'll scare them half to death.

00:54:19.278 --> 00:54:20.988
Whoever gives you a hard time,

00:54:21.072 --> 00:54:23.407
don't forget that
I won't let them get away with it.

00:54:24.950 --> 00:54:27.661
Hold your head high
and don't let anyone intimidate you.

00:54:29.330 --> 00:54:30.915
What's the last thing?

00:54:38.714 --> 00:54:39.632
Here.

00:54:45.012 --> 00:54:47.264
If one day, out of the blue,

00:54:48.724 --> 00:54:52.186
you ever find yourself really missing me,
open it then.

00:54:56.273 --> 00:54:57.358
I will.

00:54:59.777 --> 00:55:02.404
Is there anything you want to tell me?

00:55:05.241 --> 00:55:06.742
I'll say three things too.

00:55:09.745 --> 00:55:10.579
First,

00:55:12.623 --> 00:55:14.375
learn to be a little more cowardly.

00:55:15.000 --> 00:55:17.419
Don't jump into others' troubles
and end up in handcuffs.

00:55:17.962 --> 00:55:19.588
When you see injustice, hold back.

00:55:19.672 --> 00:55:21.173
Hold your tongue.

00:55:21.841 --> 00:55:22.675
Okay?

00:55:23.968 --> 00:55:25.177
I'll keep that in mind.

00:55:27.930 --> 00:55:28.889
For the second one...

00:55:36.814 --> 00:55:38.649
Don't wear a suit in front of other women.

00:55:40.151 --> 00:55:41.360
Why a suit...

00:55:45.781 --> 00:55:46.866
I won't.

00:55:47.491 --> 00:55:51.328
I'll put my suit in the closet
until the day I see you again,

00:55:52.037 --> 00:55:53.247
and then I'll wear it.

00:55:55.791 --> 00:55:56.834
What's the last one?

00:56:01.589 --> 00:56:02.631
Nothing.

00:56:04.049 --> 00:56:04.884
There isn't one?

00:56:06.844 --> 00:56:09.180
The last one is pointless anyway.

00:56:12.766 --> 00:56:13.726
I'll go, then.

00:56:14.810 --> 00:56:17.605
Are we really... saying goodbye here?

00:56:20.065 --> 00:56:20.941
Goodbye.

00:56:23.652 --> 00:56:24.862
Okay. Take care, Ms. Bom.

00:56:26.447 --> 00:56:27.448
No.

00:56:27.531 --> 00:56:30.910
I guess I need to change
how I address you now, right?

00:56:35.206 --> 00:56:38.709
Well then, goodbye, Ms. Yoon Bom.

00:56:40.711 --> 00:56:42.129
Take care,

00:56:43.631 --> 00:56:44.757
Han-gyul's uncle.

00:57:21.794 --> 00:57:22.836
Mr. Sun.

00:57:24.755 --> 00:57:25.839
Yes, Ms. Bom.

00:57:26.840 --> 00:57:28.342
There's still 20 seconds left.

00:57:29.051 --> 00:57:32.012
Can I say what I couldn't earlier?

00:57:33.430 --> 00:57:34.265
Sure.

00:57:35.266 --> 00:57:36.225
What is it?

00:57:38.269 --> 00:57:39.436
Can you...

00:57:40.729 --> 00:57:41.897
give me...

00:57:46.485 --> 00:57:47.778
one last hug?

00:58:03.627 --> 00:58:05.713
DANGER
KEEP OUT

00:59:53.320 --> 00:59:55.114
Are you crying, Mr. Sun?

00:59:55.197 --> 00:59:58.117
Now that you know I'm okay, stop crying.

00:59:58.200 --> 00:59:59.993
Is there someone you're into?

01:00:02.538 --> 01:00:04.331
His uncle... got knocked down?

01:00:04.415 --> 01:00:06.291
Did Jae-gyu say I came to sell insurance?

01:00:06.375 --> 01:00:07.668
That's impressive.

01:00:07.751 --> 01:00:10.712
I just ran into that woman,
so tell me the truth.

01:00:10.796 --> 01:00:12.840
-Were you with Ms. Bom?
-She came to my office.

01:00:12.923 --> 01:00:15.092
Forget that. Where is she right now?

01:00:15.175 --> 01:00:16.260
Ms. Bom!

01:00:17.261 --> 01:00:18.345
Ms. Bom!

